Help Type: command
Command: spinedigest

SpineDigest CLI

Purpose:
  Build portable LLM Wiki archives for AI agents.
  Treat `.sdpub` as the primary knowledge archive: import sources, build derived knowledge, then search, browse, read source fragments, navigate links, and export projections without unpacking it.

Three exploration modes:
  1. Search mode:
     Use `find` for whitespace-separated keyword discovery and `grep` for exact continuous text.
     Untyped `find` is broad candidate discovery. For content understanding, choose a search lens:
       --type node      topology / LLM Wiki structure
       --type summary   quick overview
       --type fragment  original source wording
  2. Structure mode:
     Use `list` to get bounded object collections and `page` to open one detailed object with local navigation.
  3. Reading mode:
     Use `read` to print chapter, summary, fragment, or node text as continuous plain text.

Task routing:
  For synthesis, timelines, relationship analysis, process reconstruction, or concept-structure tasks, start with Structure mode:
    status -> index -> list --type chapter -> page chapter:<id>
  Use broad `find` to locate candidate chapters or verify missing concepts, then add a search lens (`--type node|summary|fragment`) for content judgments. Use `grep` only for exact source wording.

Archive-first usage:
  spinedigest import <archive.sdpub> [source] [--input-format <format>] [--llm <json>] [--prompt <text>]
  spinedigest build <archive.sdpub> [--stage <source|graph|summary|ready>] [--chapter <id>] [--llm <json>] [--prompt <text>] [--confirm]
  spinedigest estimate <archive.sdpub> [--stage <source|graph|summary|ready>] [--json]
  spinedigest status <archive.sdpub> [--json]
  spinedigest index <archive.sdpub> [--json]
  spinedigest list <archive.sdpub> [--id <ids>] [--chapter <ids>] [--type <types>] [--limit <n>] [--cursor <token>] [--json]
  spinedigest find <archive.sdpub> <query> [--match <any|all>] [--type <node|summary|fragment>] [--json]
  spinedigest grep <archive.sdpub> <query> [--json]
  spinedigest page <archive.sdpub> <id> [--json]
  spinedigest read <archive.sdpub> <id>
  spinedigest links <archive.sdpub> <node:id> [--json]
  spinedigest backlinks <archive.sdpub> <node:id> [--json]
  spinedigest related <archive.sdpub> <node:id> [--json]
  spinedigest path <archive.sdpub> <node:id> <node:id> --chapter <id>
  spinedigest pack <archive.sdpub> <id> [--budget <chars>] [--json]
  spinedigest export <archive.sdpub> --output-format <format> [--output <path>]

Direct digest command:
  `spinedigest transform` is the direct one-shot digest/export command.
  It reads from `--input <path>`, or from stdin when `--input` is omitted.
  It writes to `--output <path>`, or to stdout when `--output` is omitted.
  A bare non-interactive `spinedigest` invocation still runs the same direct digest command for compatibility.
  Prefer the archive-first commands for new automation.

Direct and maintenance usage:
  spinedigest transform [--input <path>] [--output <path>] [--input-format <format>] [--output-format <format>] [--digest-dir <path>] [--llm <json>] [--prompt <text>] [--stage <stage>] [--verbose|-v] [--help|-h]
  spinedigest meta <archive.sdpub> [metadata options] [--json] [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  spinedigest cover <archive.sdpub> [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  spinedigest chapter <action> <archive.sdpub> [options] [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  spinedigest config status [--llm <json>] [--help|-h]
  spinedigest help [topic] [--help|-h]

  Maintenance commands are for metadata, cover extraction, and chapter tree edits. Routine archive exploration should use `index`, `list`, `page`, `find`, `grep`, and `read`.

Core object ids:
  chapter:<id>     A chapter-like archive page.
  node:<id>        A graph knowledge node.
  fragment:a:b     A source reading fragment.
  summary:<id>     A chapter summary projection.
  meta:book        Archive metadata.

Cost contract:
  Import is cheap when it stops at source.
  List, search, page, read, links, and export are cheap after build.
  Build can call an LLM and may be expensive. Run `spinedigest estimate <archive.sdpub>` before full-archive graph, summary, or ready builds, then rerun `build` with `--confirm`.

Help contract:
  - Append `--help` to commands and subcommands to see command-specific usage.
  - Use `spinedigest help <topic>` for cross-command concepts, constraints, and runtime behavior.
  - Treat `spinedigest --help` as the root page of the same help system.

Search lens examples:
  spinedigest find book.sdpub "keyword"
    Broad first pass across metadata, chapter titles, summaries, nodes, and fragments.
  spinedigest find book.sdpub "keyword" --type node
    Topology / LLM Wiki structure.
  spinedigest find book.sdpub "keyword" --type summary
    Quick overview.
  spinedigest find book.sdpub "keyword" --type fragment
    Original source wording.

